               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa ʾaślǝṭi, Lectionary for the week (fols. 4ra-28rb) 
 II)
                     Bārǝkanna ʾǝgziʾo… “Bless us, O Lord…” (Blessing prayer) (fols. 28rb-29va)
                     
 Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="4ra" to="29vb"/>
                     <title>መጽፍ፡ አስልጥ፡ (Maṣḥaf ʾaslǝṭ)</title>
                     
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="4ra" to="28rb"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1917Mashaf#week">Maṣḥafa ʾaślǝṭi, Lectionary for the week</title>
   
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="28rb" to="29va"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5655BarekannaEgzio">Bārǝkanna ʾǝgziʾo</title>
                        
                        
                     </msItem>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1"> 
                        <locus target="#39vb"/> ዝመጽፍ[sic]፡ አስልጥ፡ ዘ፯ቱ፡ ዕለት፡ ዘአባ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡
                        ወአቡሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወአሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ብርሃን፡ ዘአጥረያ፡ ንዋዩ[sic]፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡
                        በ፲ወ፱፻፸ወ፪ቱ፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ተጽሐፈ። <note>The colophon mentions that the
                        Ms. is in the possession of (but appareantly meaning: commissioned by) Takla
                        Hāymānot, was written in 1972 A.M. (= 1979-80 A.D.). The relatives of Takla
                        Hāymānot(his father Yoḥannǝs and his mother Walatta Bǝrhān) are also mentioned.</note>
                        
                        <note>The entire work (Texts I-II) is called <title><foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽፍ፡ አስልጥ፡</foreign> Maṣḥaf ʾaslǝṭ</title> in the colophon</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
